SKOS_CONCEPT.alt_label: Binding Antidrug Antibody
SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: A measurement of the binding antidrug antibody in a biological specimen. A binding antidrug antibody is an antibody that binds to a test article, and/or portion(s) of the test article.
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Binding Antidrug Antibody Measurement

SKOS_CONCEPT.alt_label: Neutralizing Binding Antidrug Antibody
SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: A measurement of the neutralizing binding antidrug antibody in a biological specimen. A neutralizing binding antidrug antibody is a type of ADA that binds to the functional portion of a test article leading to diminished or negated pharmacological activity.
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Neutralizing Binding Antidrug Antibody Measurement

SKOS_CONCEPT.alt_label: Neutraliz Cross-React Bind Antidrug AB;Neutralizing Cross-Reactive Binding Antidrug Antibody
SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: A measurement of the neutralizing cross-reactive binding antidrug antibody in a biological specimen. A neutralizing cross-reactive binding antidrug antibody is a type of ADA that binds to an endogenous molecule that is structurally similar to an analogue test article and diminishes or negates its function.
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Neutralizing Cross-Reacting Binding Antidrug Antibody Measurement

SKOS_CONCEPT.alt_label: Cross-Reactive Binding Antidrug Antibody

SKOS_CONCEPT.alt_label: Functional Microbial-induced Antibody
SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: A measurement of the functional binding microbial-induced antibody in a biological specimen. A functional microbial-induced antibody is defined as antibodies that have agonist or antagonist effects on pathogens or their toxins in the presence of other effector molecules or cells. For example, the effects of functional antibodies can include neutralization, phagocytosis, antibody-dependent cellular cytotoxicity, and complement-mediated lysis. The production of this antibody may be triggered by naturally occurring infection and/or vaccination using a whole microbe or component(s) of a microbe.
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Functional Microbial-induced Antibody Measurement

SKOS_CONCEPT.alt_label: Microbial-induced IgG Antibody
SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: A measurement of the binding microbial-induced IgG antibody in a biological specimen; the production of this antibody may be triggered by naturally occurring infection and/or vaccination using a whole microbe or component(s) of a microbe.
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Microbial-induced IgG Antibody Measurement

SKOS_CONCEPT.alt_label: Neutralizing Microbial-induced Antibody
SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: A measurement of the neutralizing binding microbial-induced antibody in a biological specimen. A neutralizing microbial-induced antibody is a type of functional antibody that's defined as antibodies that bind to, block and prevent microbes from infecting cells. The production of this antibody may be triggered by naturally occurring infection and/or vaccination using a whole microbe or component(s) of a microbe.
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Neutralizing Microbial-induced Antibody Measurement

SKOS_CONCEPT.alt_label: Total IgG Antibody Secreting Cells;Total IgG ASCs
SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: A measurement of the total IgG antibody secreting cells in a biological specimen.
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: Total IgG Antibody Secreting Cell Count

SKOS_CONCEPT.alt_label: T-Lymphocyte Proliferation Index
SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: A relative measurement (ratio or percentage) of T-lymphocyte proliferation due to stimulation by an antigen of interest to a non-stimulated T-lymphocyte proliferation control.
SKOS_CONCEPT.pref_label: T-Lymphocyte Proliferation Index
